To whom it may concern

I recently found the wonderful research tools Scribe and Zotero. While
it seems that many are migrating from Scribe over to Zotero I would
like to use both of them. This is because I really need Scribes
ability to handle author and event cards in some cases. Zotero on the
other hand is perfect for retrieving references while searching the
Internet. I have tried all the export formats in Zoteros pull down
menu and I can't get any of them imported to Scribe. The only way I
have managed to get a reference from Zotero to Scibe is via EndNote,
but that isn't really efficient. So it would be really helpful if
anybody has any suggestions about how I could solve this.

I hope my English has been understandable.

Greetings from a Norwegian history student.
</POST>
