Thank you for the response Elena.

I have tried exporting from Zotero in RIS format and importing using
&quot;Import Bibliographic Citation&quot; option again. This works only
partially though. I have tried some different exports from Zotero
(that is exporting only one item, several items, different items and
so on) and have found some problems:

1. Books that have been imported to Scribe only have the authors last
name (i.e. the first name doesn't import?).
2. Book titles get amputated after comma. So every thing after the
comma is left out.
3. A problem for me using Norwegian references is that the Norwegian
characters æ, ø, å gets scrambled. They work fine i Zotero, but
doesn't get imported well.
4. While importing reference for video recording all the information
except publisher and release disappear(?).

I have also tried importing the same RIS files to EndNote and they
work much better there. The names get correct and even keywords get
imported. So it seems it's Scribes import feature that's not working
properly(?).

If it is possible to fix any of this it would be great. And I would
also like to import tags and notes. It would pretty much be fine to
import as much as possible.

And I'm on a Mac.

Thanks,
Fredrik

